<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/489921-would-this-be-appropriate-for-a-fifteen">Would this be appropriate for a fifteen year old? In other words, does it have graphic sexual description--which would be inappropriate? Thanks.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_489921'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F102720.Roman_Blood">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/489921-would-this-be-appropriate-for-a-fifteen">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/489921-would-this-be-appropriate-for-a-fifteen">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4253494-rona"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1599775659i/4253494._UY100_CR21,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4253494-rona">Rona</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The sex scenes are detailed. One scene plays over and over in the memory of the main character; that scene involves an adolescent girl. There is inces<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The sex scenes are detailed. One scene plays over and over in the memory of the main character; that scene involves an adolescent girl. There is incest. There is consensual adult sexuality. There is a highly nuanced exploration of slavery in the Roman time.<br />Not for a typical fifteen year old. <br />If you want this child to read about Rome, maybe go to the Lindsey Davis series with the Roman detective Marcus Didius Falco. He has lots of sex, but it is done with fade-out, not details. He has a disapproving mother and a big extended family. He has money problems. A child might find him easy to relate to because he has a good bit of hapless adolescent in him. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link738817" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=738817&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F489921-would-this-be-appropriate-for-a-fifteen%2Fanswers%2F738817-the-sex-scenes-are">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

